# Windsurf rules for strucmod project

This project follows the strucmod pipeline. Read AGENTS.md as the
primary instruction source. Plugin files (skills, agents, rules) live at
`<plugin-root>/`, typically `.claude/plugins/strucmod/`.

Mandatory reading:
- AGENTS.md
- <plugin-root>/skills/strucmod/SKILL.md
- <plugin-root>/rules/orchestrator-protocol.md
- <plugin-root>/rules/plan-first-modeling.md
- <plugin-root>/rules/academic-writing-style.md
- <plugin-root>/rules/numerical-validation-protocol.md
- <plugin-root>/rules/replication-protocol.md
- <plugin-root>/rules/modeling-coding-conventions.md

Hard constraints:
- Never write parameter values without a documented source in code/01_calibration.csv.
- Never invoke a solver without spec.md + model-reviewer approval.
- Never modify code/seed.txt, .gitignore, or paper/main.tex casually.
- All manuscript prose follows academic-writing-style: no file paths, no pipeline terms, no bash commands.
- Use relative paths; code comments default to Chinese.
